My Favorite Skincare Tips for Healthy, Glowing Skin!! 
- Always invest in professional or medical grade skin care. 
They are made in small batches.
They have higher levels of active ingredients.
They are designed for maximum penetration. 
They contain pH-adjusted ingredients.
They may contain prescription-strength ingredients
They are priced more honestly.

- Vitamin C 
Is safe for most skin types
Provides hydration
Brightens your skin
Reduces redness
Reduces hyperpigmentation
Promotes collagen production
Helps to prevent sagging
Protects against sun damage
Helps with wound healing

- Sunscreen 
Skin cancer can be prevented with the use of sunscreen.
Premature aging can be avoided with the use of sunscreen 
Hyperpigmentation is less likely with the use of sunscreen.
The use of sunscreen helps to keep the skin from becoming inflamed.
Sunscreen helps to avoid sun sensitivity.

If you are new to the self care as skin care world, these products are a must and if you’d like yo learn more, please message me. I would be elated to work with you and your skin care journey! 
❤️
Kate B 
Your Estie Bestie

That look you make because you know it’s chemical peel season!! 🎉🎊🥳
Now is the perfect time to revisit chemical peels, especially if you are looking for a holiday glow up this winter!! 
Not all chemical peels are the same, some involve deep peeling, and others exfoliate the top few layers of the skin with no downtime! 
Personally, I am the type of client who can only do light  chemical peels such as a mandelic acid peel, due to the sensitive nature of my skin type. 
However individual skin types vary and some skin types  can accept a more aggressive treatment! 
Message me today to book your free chemical peel consultation so we can find out which #chemicalpeel works best for your skin type! 
Remember folks the skin is our largest organ in our bodies and we need to care for it! 
Let me assist you along that journey!

As the year comes to a close and I reflect on all the ups and downs of the past year, I’m reminded of the quote from Theodore Roosevelt 
“Believe you can and you’re halfway there." 
This rings true in good times and bad, faith, family & gratitude  is the vehicle that will get you through. 
Over the last year, health problems have become the forefront of priority, being in the hospital more this year than my whole life has been an  eye opening experience. 
Blood transfusions, iron fusions and surgery, really make you appreciate the little things in life and to live life to the fullest! 
Along with all the unexpected, my sister @nattymak birthed a beautiful baby girl, now our family circle is complete! 
Oh what JOY LITTLE GIRLS BRING! 💕🌸💞
I’m grateful beyond measure for my husband, family and friends! 
They are the inspiration and motivation that keep these feet moving forward, even when I’m wallowing in the muck! 
Take time today to reflect on how far you’ve come, appreciate the little wins and remember to believe you can you are half way there! 
Wishing you all a healthy and prosperous new year! 
♥️
Kate B
